<div class="content">
  <h1>TwitterFon Bookmarklet Setup</h1>
  <div class="cell">
    <p>
    You're here, so let's install the bookmarklet directly onto your iPhone!
    </p>
  </div>
  <h2>
    Step 1: Bookmark this page
  </h2>
  <div class="cell">
    <p>
      Tap the add button at the bottom of the screen, make a note of the name and bookmarks folder, then click Save.
    </p>
    <p>
      <img src="add_bookmark.png" style="width: 280px;" alt="add bookmark button"/>
    </p>
    <p>
      <img src="save_bookmark.png" style="width: 280px" alt="save bookmark" />
    </p>
  </div>
  <h2>
    Step 2: Edit the Bookmark
  </h2>
  <div class="cell">
  <p>
    Tap the Bookmarks button at the bottom of the screen, navigate through your Bookmarks folders until you find the new bookmark. <strong>Click Edit.</strong>
  </p>
  <p>
    <img src="open_bookmark.png" style="width: 280px;" alt="edit bookmark"/>
  </p>
  <p>
    Tap the address in the second field, then tap-drag all the way to the left, this will take a few seconds.
  </p>

  <p>
    <img src="edit_bookmark.png" style="width: 280px" alt="delete this text"/>
  </p>
  <p>
    Place the editing point after the blue-shaded text, between the "?" and the j in "javascript", then tap and hold down the delete key.
  </p>
  <p>
    That's it! You've enabled the bookmarklet, enjoy!
  </p>
</div>
	
